                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1761: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-23T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. Your September 19, 9 p.m.</p>
                <p>Before reaching decision regarding request to increase number of marines now
                    stationed at Camaguey, Department desires information as to why you have reason
                    to believe that the lives and property of American citizens in Camaguey will be
                    endangered during electoral period. Please cable full report.</p>
                <p>Department regrets that it is unable to approve your request that officers from
                    the Marine Corps be used for intelligence duty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
